<script id="logo-script" type="text/javascript">
var ready = false
var timeText

function build(){
    $("#top-bar-clock").remove();
    var topbar = $('.md-toolbar-tools');
    var div =  $('<div/>');
    var p = $('<p/ id="top-bar-clock", class="top-bar-txt">');
    div.append(p);
    div[0].style.margin = '5px 5px 5px auto';
    topbar.append(div);
    
    //$('<div />').attr({id:"top-bar-clock",class:"top-bar-txt"}).appendTo(topbar); 
}
// these functions can be called any time from server side
// if DOM is not ready, just store the variable
function showTime(time){
    if(time){
        timeText = time
    }
    if(!ready){
        return
    }
    $("#top-bar-clock").text(timeText)
}

function checkExistence(){
    if($("#top-bar-clock").length > 0){
        ready = true
        // call updateTitle cos server may have called it before DOM is ready 
        showTime()
        return
    }
    build()
    setTimeout(checkExistence,100)
}

build()
setTimeout(checkExistence,100)

// expose api's
window.TopBar = {
    updateTime:showTime
}
</script>

format:
<script>
    (function(scope) {
  scope.$watch('msg', function(msg) {
    if (msg) {
        // call exposed api's  
        if(msg.topic == "clock"){
            window.TopBar.updateTime(msg.payload)
        }
    }
  });
})(scope);
</script>
